    "Long Description": "9.38 VISUAL and UTG TEST. Work scope:1) Visual Inspection: (1 Visual Inspector for 1 man-day work): a. Perform visual inspection to all accessible area of existing water pipe to check for external sign of corrosion, leakages and damages, b.All anomalies observed will be recorded by digital photograph and reported in our inspection report, c.To randomly select up to 30 nos. of UTG test location of water pipe for the UTG inspector to perform thickness measurement.2) Ultrasonic Thickness Gauging (1 UTG Inspector for 1 manday work):a.Perform UTG test on the 30 selected locations of water pipe to ascertain the current wall thickness. Each location to test 4 utg points at 0, 90, 180 and 270 degree orientation, b.Provide UTG report identifying the location tested. 3) Evaluation Report: a.Provide VI and UTG report with evaluation of result in accordance with applicable standard for piping. Evaluation report includes the calculation of corrosion rate and remaining life of the piping based on the results obtained by UTG test,b.Provide recommendation for work improvement, repair or replacement on any anomalies observed.4) Work Schedule:a.1st day visit - Visual inspection to all accessible areas of water pipe, b.1st day visit - UTG test to be performed on the 30 nos. of selected location, c.Submission of Visual and UTG test reports - 1 week after work completion at site.",
